#: of numpy.std:85
msgid ":ref:`ufuncs-output-type`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:89
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:90
msgid ""
"There are several common variants of the array standard deviation "
"calculation. Assuming the input `a` is a one-dimensional NumPy array and "
"``mean`` is either provided as an argument or computed as ``a.mean()``, "
"NumPy computes the standard deviation of an array as::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:95
msgid ""
"N = len(a)\n"
"d2 = abs(a - mean)**2  # abs is for complex `a`\n"
"var = d2.sum() / (N - ddof)  # note use of `ddof`\n"
"std = var**0.5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:100
msgid ""
"Different values of the argument `ddof` are useful in different contexts. "
"NumPy's default ``ddof=0`` corresponds with the expression:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:103
msgid "\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2 }}{N}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:107
msgid ""
"which is sometimes called the \"population standard deviation\" in the field "
"of statistics because it applies the definition of standard deviation to `a` "
"as if `a` were a complete population of possible observations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:111
msgid ""
"Many other libraries define the standard deviation of an array differently, "
"e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:114
msgid "\\sqrt{\\frac{\\sum_i{|a_i - \\bar{a}|^2 }}{N - 1}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:118
msgid ""
"In statistics, the resulting quantity is sometimes called the \"sample "
"standard deviation\" because if `a` is a random sample from a larger "
"population, this calculation provides the square root of an unbiased "
"estimate of the variance of the population. The use of :math:`N-1` in the "
"denominator is often called \"Bessel's correction\" because it corrects for "
"bias (toward lower values) in the variance estimate introduced when the "
"sample mean of `a` is used in place of the true mean of the population. The "
"resulting estimate of the standard deviation is still biased, but less than "
"it would have been without the correction. For this quantity, use ``ddof=1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:129
msgid ""
"Note that, for complex numbers, `std` takes the absolute value before "
"squaring, so that the result is always real and nonnegative."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.std:132
msgid ""
"For floating-point input, the standard deviation is computed using the same "
"precision the input has. Depending on the input data, this can cause the "
"results to be inaccurate, especially for float32 (see example below). "
"Specifying a higher-accuracy accumulator using the `dtype` keyword can "
"alleviate this issue."
msgstr ""

